Sentencas: Room temperature crystal structure, electrical properties and electrochemical properties in the temperature range 25-700 degrees C of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+delta prepared by acetate combustion is investigated from intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell cathode viewpoint.
Titulo: Crystal structure, electrical and electrochemical properties of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+δ mixed ionic-electronic conductors (MIECs)

Sentencas: The Pr1.3Sr0.7Ni1-xCuxO4+delta (PSNCO) solid solutions have a tetragonal I4/mmm K2NiF4-type structure which consists of a (Pr1.3Sr0.7) (Ni1.xCux)O-3 perovskite unit and a (Pr1.3Sr0.7)O rock salt unit in the whole compositional range 0
Titulo: Crystal structure, electrical and electrochemical properties of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+δ mixed ionic-electronic conductors (MIECs)
Crystal structure, electrical and electrochemical properties of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+δ mixed ionic-electronic conductors (MIECs)

Sentencas: A reduction in bond-length of Ni/Cu-O resulting from PSNCO lattice contraction eases hop of small polaron from Ni3+ to Ni2+/Cu2+ in (Ni1-xCux)-O layer with low activation energy, which increases electron conductivity.
Titulo: Crystal structure, electrical and electrochemical properties of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+δ mixed ionic-electronic conductors (MIECs)

Sentencas: The maximum electronic conductivity (sigma = Omega cm(-1)) with minimum activation energy (E-a = eV) is observed at x = 0.3.
Titulo: Crystal structure, electrical and electrochemical properties of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+δ mixed ionic-electronic conductors (MIECs)

Sentencas: Lattice expansion along c-direction owing to Cu2+ doping facilitates hop of O2+ from its occupied interstitial site (O3) to nearby equivalent site assisted by anisotropic thermal motion of apical oxygen O2 resulting in increase in ionic conductivity.
Titulo: Crystal structure, electrical and electrochemical properties of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+δ mixed ionic-electronic conductors (MIECs)

Sentencas: The minimum polarization resistance value (R-p = 0.13 (2) Omega cm(2)) and activation energy (E-a = 1.321 (5) eV) at x = 0.3 is attributed to high electronic and ionic conductivities compared to other compositions.
Titulo: Crystal structure, electrical and electrochemical properties of Cu co-doped Pr1.3Sr0.7NiO4+δ mixed ionic-electronic conductors (MIECs)

Sentencas: Complex impedance spectroscopy studies suggest that the ORR is co-limited by O2- diffusion and O-2 surface exchange.
